It took me 2 hours of reading thru the entire `man cmake` and bunch of trial and error and the solution turned out to be pretty silly lol.

@hsanson Could you also double check that this fix also works on the latest master branch?

Tho I'm not exactly sure cmake is installed in that location for every distribution, so I think we need something a bit more clever than `echo` like `which cmake`? Assuming that which is installed on every system.

@dundargoc I'll hand it to someone who's more knowledgeable in this space. ~~I'm a python dev :P~~

@dundargoc latest  master works. 

Since the real issue is a miss-configuration from my side I apologize for the trouble and time. 

Looking at my config I am adding an env variable to my PATH that is never set. This results in PATH having an empty "" entry in the list of paths that gets interpreted as `current path`. This is what causes make to resolve `cmake` to that folder instead of `/usr/bin/cmake`.
